        "name": "Shrikant Shrihari Mundhe",
        "playerID": "3994",
        "birthPlace": "India",
        "dob": "27/10/1988",
        "description": "<p>Shrikant Mundhe, a right-hand batsman and a right-arm medium pacer represents Maharashtra in domestic cricket. After a forgettable first-class debut in the year 2007 against Tamil Nadu, he emerged as Maharashtra’s leading wicket-taker in the 2010-11 season with 21 scalps and scored 218 runs. He has also played for India Red in the Challenger Trophy. Mundhe was signed by the Pune Warriors India in the 2011 IPL.</p>",
