        "name": "Faisal Iqbal",
        "playerID": "1084",
        "birthPlace": "Pakistan",
        "dob": "30/12/1981",
        "description": "<p>Faisal Iqbal is an exciting middle-order batsman from Pakistan. A flamboyant stroke player with sound defence, Iqbal was a prolific run-scorer at the junior level which prompted his move into the Test team.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHowever, Iqbal's entry into the Test team was criticized on grounds of favouritism - he happens to be Javed Miandad's nephew. But he demonstrated that he was worth that Test cap with an aggressive counter-attacking 83 off 85 balls in the first Test against Australia in Colombo in 2002-03.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHis failure at the top level saw him disappear from the national side for many years. He made a comeback in 2005-06 and since then, has been in the scheme of things for Pakistan.</p>",
