        "playerID": "1334",
        "birthPlace": "Bangladesh",
        "dob": "17/08/1972",
        "description": "<p>Captained Bangladesh to their victory over Australia, at Cardiff, during the 2005 Natwest Series, having replaced Khaled Mahmud at the start of the 2003/4 series against Zimbabwe.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMissed the 2004 ICC Champions Trophy with a broken thumb.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHas yet to score an ODI century, but during the 2005/6 season he averaged 37.77 from 13 matches, scoring 340 runs.</p>",
