        "birthPlace": "Nevis",
        "dob": "22/07/1978",
        "description": "<p>Runako Morton is a lively, unpredictable and controversial cricketer from West Indies. His career has many black remarks for his controversies, off and on the field. Morton proved his worth by scoring two tons in successive ODI series but has found it difficult to maintain a regular fixture into the team in the past couple of years. Runako Morton has the dubious record of the slowest ODI duck which lasted 31 balls in the final of the DFL Cup against Australia in 2006.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOn 4th March 2012, Runako Morton was unfortunately involved in a car crash and lost his life.</p>",
