        "description": "<p>A genuine left arm swing bowler, Saimullah Khan boasts of an enviable record in Pakistan's domestic league. With an astonishing average of 18.78, Khan has 379 victims in 82 first-class games to his name. His phenomenal rise in the domestic circuit saw him earn an ODI place in Pakistan's national side against Zimbabwe in 2008 and featured in a couple of ODIs. Unfortunately, Khan went wicket-less in both games and a spate of injuries saw him lose his place in the squad.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNow at 31, an international call looks a bit unlikely but the job he has done for the Faisalabad Wolves cannot be underestimated. In the fifth edition of the Champions League T20 in India, he would look to do more of the same for the Wolves.</p>",
