        "description": "<p>Run out in two of his first four ODIs. Scored his first ODI half-century against Bangladesh in 2007. Made 40 against New Zealand in the ICC CWC 2007, having also scored 41 against Kenya. Was the top scorer for his team against Bermuda in the ICC World Twenty20 Qualifier 2008 scoring 31 in 34 balls. Canada won the game by eight wickets. Averaged 25.24 in the 2007-08 State Shield competition for Central Districts and scored two half-centuries, and averaged over 50 in the State Championship in the 2006/7 season.</p>",
