        "name": "Pradeep Jaibeer Sangwan",
        "playerID": "4280",
        "birthPlace": "India",
        "dob": "05/11/1990",
        "description": "<p>A left-arm medium pacer, Pradeep Sangwan made his first-class debut for Delhi in the Ranji Trophy season of 2007-08, with 33 wickets at a decent average of 19.24. This won him a spot in the Indian team for the U-19 World Cup in Malaysia, where he impressed everyone with his seam and swing bowling and his 5 for 44 was instrumental in India’s win against South Africa at the group stage.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn 2008, he was picked by the Delhi Daredevils for the first IPL season and was later bought by the Kolkata Knight Riders in 2011.</p>",
