        "birthPlace": "Australia",
        "dob": "08/11/1984",
        "description": "<p>After an awful first-class debut in 2007-08, Nathan Reardon who is often known as “Reardo” has shown signs of a good stylish left handed batsman who can bowl a bit. With a few handful seasons and just a couple of centuries amongst First Class and List A matches Nathan has paved his way finding a middle order spot for Queensland. He has also played for Melbourne Renegades and is not only known for his batting but also excels in fielding.</p>",
