        "description": "<p>Eklavya Dwivedi is a right-hand batsman and a wicket-keeper from the state of Uttar Pradesh. He made his first-class debut for the state in 2010 against Orissa. He played a crucial innings of 83 in his first innings.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHe was grabbed by the Pune Warriors India for the fourth season of the IPL in 2011.</p>",
