        "description": "<p>England have never been short of talent in the fast bowling department and the new kid on the block, Moin Ashraf is a prime example of it. With the potential to become a fearful strike bowler, Ashraf proved his talent in only his second appearance for Yorkshire in 2010 where he bagged the first-innings figures of 5-32 against Kent. However, he failed to match his initial performance; the national selectors showed confidence in his ability and included him for the 2011/12 Potential England Performance Programme Squad. One of the quickest bowlers for Yorkshire, Ashraf was in the squad for the Champions League T20, 2012.</p>",
