        "birthPlace": "Netherlands",
        "dob": "19/10/1982",
        "description": "<p>Played for Middlesex in the Twenty20 Cup in 2004. Played at the ICC CWC 2003, scoring 62 against India and taking 3-16 against England, including the wickets of Nick Knight, Michael Vaughan and Andrew Flintoff. Scored 291 runs at an average of 48.50 at ICC Trophy in Ireland in 2005. Scored 237 runs at an average of 33.85 at ICC CWC Qualifier in South Africa in April this year. Made his best ODI score of 80 against Kenya at Potchefstroom during the ICC CWC Qualifier 2009.</p>",
