        "description": "<p>A right-hand batsman and wicketkeeper, Mohammad Salman played first-class cricket for Faisalabad in Pakistan for over a decade since 1999 before being picked for the national team. His brilliant stint at the domestic level as a wicketkeeper led former Pakistani cricketer Rashid Latif to believe that he had the best wicket-keeping technique in Pakistan and that he deserves to play at the international level. Consequently, Salman made his international debut against West Indies in an ODI match in 2011.</p>",
